        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Overexpression of M6a increases number of synapses in primary hippocampal cultures (Fig. 4). Two single nucleotide polymorphisms (F93C and I97S) impair this function (Fig.5).. Experimental description: \"Dissociated neuronal cultures were prepared from rat hippocampi of embryonic day 19, as previously described (Formoso et al., 2015).\". p. 96" ;
